        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/c6cbf5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-11T22:07:00.892Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Dear Signal developers, I have an idea that would give your messenger app a truly unique selling point. The idea is as follows: There are numerous Signal groups at our daycare center and school. Parents use these groups to communicate and discuss important matters. However, teachers and educators are not part of the group, and for good reason. They should not be disturbed during the school day, and sometimes the group also discusses matters concerning them, so it is strictly a parents‚Äô group. However, teachers and educators often have important things to communicate as well. To do so, they always have to use email. However, emails are often not noticed immediately, so someone always has to copy the email from the parents to the Signal group. This is exactly where I would like to start: it would be fantastic if other Signal users could be authorized to send important messages to the group without being members of that group themselves. So, for example, if the first lesson is canceled tomorrow, the class teacher could simply send a message to the Signal group without being able to read what else is being discussed there. That would be really great! I would be very happy if you could implement this feature in the future.<br>\nBest regards<br>\nTimo</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2026-01-11T22:07:00.892Z",
