        "username": "rassilon1963",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-12T12:41:27.790Z",
        "cooked": "<p>this could already be very easily achieved with near identical results by the teacher doing one of the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>joining the group, having it muted and archived, and only entering it when they need to send an announcement.</li>\n<li>having the group link saved and just enter it to send a single message and immediately exist, repeat every time there‚Äôs something to announce.</li>\n<li>have a designated parent responsible for delivering a message to the whole group on behalf of the teacher that they teacher knows they can trust.</li>\n<li>having a parent group they aren‚Äôt a member of, and an announcement group where only they can send messages with all the parents also being members.<br>\n4b. same configuration but instead of the second group a broadcast channel, which doesn‚Äôt exist yet but is one of the most popular still-open feature requests: <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/infogroups-channels-broadcast-lists/4798\" class=\"inline-onebox\">InfoGroups / Channels / Broadcast lists</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>with the pinned messages feature <a>making great progress</a> and probably being released in not too long a time, options 1-3 can also be made significantly more effective, with the announcements being far more noticeable above the noise. with option 4 regular chats and announcements are naturally separated.<br>\neither way i think this is too niche a situation with enough existing solutions to warrant a radical change to group membership infrastructure.</p>",
